<item>
            <title>[SEC-964] NullPointerException in AuthenticationTag</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-964</link>
                <project id="10040" key="SEC">Spring Security</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When the property that is accessed via the authenticationTag is not set it throws a NPE.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Example:&lt;br/&gt;
using&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;security:authentication property=&quot;principal.extendedProperty&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;on a page where the extendedProperty is not (yet) set yields a&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;java.lang.NullPointerException&lt;br/&gt;
        at org.springframework.security.taglibs.authz.AuthenticationTag.doEndTag(AuthenticationTag.java:123)&lt;br/&gt;
        at org.apache.jsp.index_jsp._jspx_meth_authz_005fauthentication_005f0(index_jsp.java:240)&lt;br/&gt;
...&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;I would suggest the following patch to make it null-safe:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;#8212; authz-orig/AuthenticationTag.java	Tue Jun 24 08:18:42 2008&lt;br/&gt;
+++ authz/AuthenticationTag.java	Wed Aug 20 15:15:58 2008&lt;br/&gt;
@@ -122,3 +122,3 @@&lt;br/&gt;
         } else &lt;/p&gt;
{
-            writeMessage(result.toString());
+            writeMessage(result==null?&quot;&quot;:result.toString());
         }</description>
